TextBlock.TextLine: Antwerp. 18 June 1681
London Will Scawen
th
S. my last to you was the 4: curitt, sence non from you, this for
covert of the inclosed invoyce for 77p. of tykes amonghst which there
are 6 2 seales foalded in 3: so that them bare butt 3 peeces and each written
up on dobbel lead, so that you will finde 74: p viz 71 single & 3 dubble
which I am informed do pass, so the pack is att bruges by this time
& hope may come with Ben: clarck now in loading there you finding the
invoyce well please to give mee creditt in yd acctt. for £138:6:8, I have rec. the rest of the
callicoes from bruges & payd the aggreement, a bad capp: & the more because wee have no
vent att present whoever I hope itt will come in time whilst I remaine
London Abram vivian
@ 18 June
th
S. my last to you was on the 14: curitt to which referre, you, sence have
recd. yd of 3: ditto where by you tell mee the bayes to beatt Hull & the kersies
all bought, the pryses of which are high, so that I hope I shall have of the best
goods as formarly desired, and could wish come with smith, which I supose
is att zea, for John nelson sealed the 3: from Hull, and arrved the
next day att ostend for which god be thanked, he hath aboard for us thes bales
N. 32„ 33 & 34 which come in good season, god send all the rest sasve & I hope
then to give an acct. to content if onely the goods prove to exspectation
I hope that m. potters providing will be as his expedition, for the laster
do not blamd him, butt when I see the goods, shall advise you the needfull
I am sensible of yd straights for mony yett I can not assist you as
I could wish, whoever beleave mee that no endeavour is want omy to take
away all manner of complaints I could finde no mony att sight for london
so remitt onely £50: att 1 ½ uso on John lambe, by him accepted for my acctt
in case you please gett itt discounted & you may charge mee wish itt I
go for Brussels after to marrow & hope to finde mony to remitt pr. next
on which you may depend the laces will come also N.15 beeng intended by
Ben: Clarck who shall part withim 3 a 4 dayes, which is the needfulle
| 18 June
th
London Henry Maynard
S. my last to you was on the 14: curitt sence non from you, so this Cheefly
for covert to the inclosed 2 bills of yd accepted. I understand that John
nelson is arrived att bruges from Hull, I wonder were smith should tarry
seeng him to have been much longer in loading then nelson, of which
yd advise, no news yett of any ships from London, butt I hope them over
by this time I do not know what do do in the concernes of
because there is no remedie to make mony for the yallow cloth, & gett
have an end to that affaire, there fore lett mee intrest you
to persuade mr. slaughter lirker to take y. back, orto press peeters for better
satisfaction I understand as if I P was dead, which I shall certainely know
intending for Brussels after to morrow & so remain
London
Francois Hertebout
Gent
mons. Den ul van 16 deser maer gisteren avont ontf. als wanneer het pak
& robbe de chambre smorgens waer geworden ick twijffe oft de 2 packen tijken
N. 15 & 16 voor nu bij ul deselve moete met alle spoet nae brugge geexgid
worden alsoo daer een Engels schip de weke vertaeht op london met dew
de selve moeten mede geladen worden daer af het gepasseirde mij laet weten
in gesloten mijn tol brief de welk voorde pagk RN9 a 13 van Brugge
komende moet dien & ul sal de 3 pack ijp onvrij verklaeren & dient
d'anderaenstonts besorgen gegevende advies vant gepassert
de pack I N. 15 & 16: ider 70 stucken stijken
@ 18 Juny
Brugge Raph: Coots:-
H in antwoort aende ul van 13„ &15 deser hebbe de cxtoene lijnwat
ontfangen, gesien tot B clarck het sijnde dese weeke sal afwncten
soo in twijffele niet oft de 2 dijck packen sullen in tijde comen & N°.15 sijnde voor
Piekerigh & Robruson In houdende 69st tijken & N°16 voor will schaden met
dt tijken a God., hebbe grand herrebouts belast de selve aen ul op 't alder spoedighst
voorts te sejnden, soo gelieft mede devoir te doen, dat de selve af geladen woorden
ende aen de vrinden het noodigh advise geeven, met exprestie in de conostementen
als geseght, icq dencke clerck het packee V. no° 15 wel sal bewaeren, daer
neghter as voor eijgen gelieft te doen. hebbe ul voor disbonso van pacq legaturen
geered., ende sal te traeta promt bess. seer geerne gesien het goet arived.

Rott, Jacques Annier
monsr. Ick hebbe op 23 past. aen ul gesonden een pack lijnweeete gemerck
voor Rek van Joan seger van Encie omsijn ordre daer mede te volgen ick
en will niet twijffelen ofte deselve sijn ul wel geworden dese alleer
om ul te versoeke dat ul de selve lijnwaeten gelieft bij te houden, tot uged
ordre vanden selve segers waer op hem sal verlaten, terwijlen van ul advies
verwaghte wat gepasseert is

thomas jmith van Hull sijn geladen de 3 gemention packen bovendien
N ATV,„ N.350 met 12 gemengelde nortse lakens N. 29 „ 30 & 31 samen met
103 p baijen sonder dat vrappers & all sonder dat ick wete pressie
